item.title: The "Cell Phones Cause Cancer" Myth That Just Won't Die
item.description:
The "Cell Phones Cause Cancer" Myth That Just Won't Die

In 1989, a New Yorker writer named Paul Brodeur published a story about Meadow Street in Guilford, Connecticut, where cancer cases had clustered near power lines and an electric substation. His influential book, called The Great Power Line Cover Up, followed in 1993.
